**The read:** Olivia Cooke as an Enneagram Type 6 — the anxious loyalist. The thesis resolves a real contradiction: the breezy, self-deprecating northern actress who "fell into" fame is the same woman who deletes Instagram to survive her own head, refuses to watch the monitor, and asks a trusted script advisor "emotionally, where am I?" She plays women fraying at the seams so well because she's fluent in it. Core tension threaded through a childhood-to-adult line ("look at me, love me" → RADA rejection → imposter tax), an empathy turn on the fame-retreat, and a callback ending on the Alicent-face joke.

